{"key":"post-11347245","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11347245</id>\n<content>&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;small&quot;&gt;Quote:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;candidguy said:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;But what I don't get is why is it 4 times bigger?&lt;br /&gt;I mean 1/8=0.125 and 1/4=.25 and that 0.125X2=.25&lt;br /&gt;so why is it 4 times and not 2 times?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;post&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The area of a circle is calculated by:&amp;nbsp; area = Pi(&lt;i&gt;r&lt;/i&gt;&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;) where Pi=3.14 and &lt;i&gt;r&lt;/i&gt;(radius) is 1/2 the diameter.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For a 1/8&quot; hole, the area is 3.14 X (.0625 X .0625) = .0122 square inch.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For a 1/4&quot; hole the area is 3.14 X (.125 X .125) = .049 square inch, which you can see is exactly four times the area of the 1/8&quot; hole.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11350335</next>\n<prev>11344023</prev>\n<first>11341920</first>\n<last>11365871</last>\n<when>1256862803</when>\n<utime>10/30/09 03:33 AM</utime>\n</post>"}